01:11.230 --> 01:14.030
(MUSIC BOX PLAYING SLOWLY)

01:33.490 --> 01:35.410
MAN: Potato Chip.

01:36.810 --> 01:38.740
Potato Chip?

01:38.780 --> 01:40.340
GIRL: I'm here!

01:40.740 --> 01:43.100
- Here I come! I'm hungry now!
- (GIRL SHRIEKS)

01:43.140 --> 01:44.980
WOMAN: Go! Run, run!

01:45.220 --> 01:47.700
- I want the Potato Chip!
- (KATIE GIGGLES)

01:47.740 --> 01:49.310
Guess who's home.

01:53.670 --> 01:56.190
(MUSIC BOX CONTINUES
PLAYING SLOWLY)

02:02.880 --> 02:04.600
TRICIA: You know, I saw the way
you were looking at her.

02:04.640 --> 02:07.000
Come on, there was a room full of writers.
I was just talking to her.

02:07.040 --> 02:09.770
Oh, come on! I know the difference
between talking and flirting.

02:09.810 --> 02:11.810
I wasn't flirting. You shoudn't've had
that third glass of wine.

02:11.850 --> 02:13.530
Oh really? Yeah, listen,
once you've been betrayed...

02:13.530 --> 02:15.130
...there's no way in the world
that I would ever...

02:15.530 --> 02:17.490
Once, Tricia, once!
Seven years ago.

02:17.530 --> 02:18.330
Once?

02:18.370 --> 02:20.300
- Once is enough for me! And...
- (HORN BLARING)

02:20.700 --> 02:24.020
- (TRICIA GASPS, SCREAMS)
- (TYRES SCREECHING)

02:26.620 --> 02:28.910
(POLICE SIRENS WAILING)

02:29.230 --> 02:30.550
(KATIE SCREAMING)

02:30.670 --> 02:31.990
Daddy!

02:37.710 --> 02:40.040
(INDISTINCT P.A. ANNOUNCEMENT)

02:40.420 --> 02:41.100
KATIE: (CRYING)
Daddy!

02:41.140 --> 02:42.860
(WEAKLY) Potato Chip...

02:44.020 --> 02:45.460
Daddy!

02:48.270 --> 02:49.910
Daddy!

02:55.350 --> 02:57.760
(MUSIC BOX CONTINUES
PLAYING SLOWLY)

03:05.440 --> 03:07.570
(CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING
OVER SPEAKER)

03:38.400 --> 03:41.880
(WATER RUNNING)

03:49.530 --> 03:51.730
(JAKE GROANS, WINCES)

04:26.440 --> 04:28.730
(MOANING LOUDLY)

04:37.540 --> 04:40.660
(JAKE CHOKING)

04:51.550 --> 04:53.950
(PANTING)

04:56.950 --> 05:00.040
The problem now is that
now you're experiencing...

05:00.040 --> 05:01.960
...a manic depressive psychosis

05:02.080 --> 05:07.210
brought on by the accident,
the brain trauma, the loss of your wife.

05:08.050 --> 05:10.610
What concerns me, Jake,
are the seizures,

05:10.650 --> 05:13.970
because those seizures are definitely a sign
of something far more serious.

05:14.010 --> 05:17.980
And if you don't at least try treatment
and give yourself a chance,

05:17.980 --> 05:20.300
you will end up
with a much worse condition.

05:22.580 --> 05:24.180
Like what?

05:24.540 --> 05:26.140
Psychotic breaks.

05:28.350 --> 05:32.550
I would like to strongly suggest
that you consider staying at St. Francis.

05:32.590 --> 05:37.920
I know doctors there. I really recommend
you get treatment for a few weeks.

05:37.920 --> 05:40.520
Maybe even a few months.

05:40.520 --> 05:42.400
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

05:42.400 --> 05:44.120
A mental hospital?

05:44.160 --> 05:45.720
Come on.

05:49.410 --> 05:52.010
I can't do that. I have a...
I have a daughter to raise.

05:52.010 --> 05:55.170
And that's exactly why you need to,

05:55.210 --> 05:57.660
because you have a daughter to raise.

06:03.580 --> 06:06.100
Still your favorite, isn't it?

06:06.700 --> 06:07.750
Yeah.

06:12.350 --> 06:13.710
Hey...

06:15.790 --> 06:17.800
Katie...

06:19.800 --> 06:22.840
I have to go away.

06:22.880 --> 06:24.000
What?

06:26.560 --> 06:28.610
Just for a little while.

06:29.010 --> 06:30.850
How long?

06:32.610 --> 06:34.730
I don't know, just a while.

06:35.650 --> 06:37.860
I wanna come.

06:39.100 --> 06:41.060
Not this time, baby.

06:41.340 --> 06:43.420
You know...

06:43.460 --> 06:48.270
the accident's made me a little bit sick
and I have to get fixed.

06:49.950 --> 06:52.790
I need to be stronger
so I can take care of you.

06:52.830 --> 06:54.430
You do!

06:56.510 --> 06:59.880
Not the way I need to, baby. Okay?

07:01.200 --> 07:04.960
You're gonna go stay with Aunt Elizabeth
and Uncle William

07:04.960 --> 07:07.290
and your cousins ​​in West Chester.

07:08.170 --> 07:11.170
(VOICE BREAKING)
But I don't want you to go!

07:13.170 --> 07:18.700
When I come back
it'll be for good, forever.

07:19.940 --> 07:21.420
It's gonna be fine.

07:43.120 --> 07:45.200
- Hey.
- Hi, sweetheart!

07:45.240 --> 07:47.210
Jake. Hi!

07:47.730 --> 07:51.770
Oh, I'm so happy you come to
stay with us.

07:52.490 --> 07:54.330
Say goodbye.

07:55.890 --> 07:58.460
- I have to go now.
- No!

07:58.460 --> 08:00.900
I'll be back soon as I can.

08:02.220 --> 08:06.780
You're my Potato Chip,
You and nobody else, okay?

08:08.750 --> 08:10.750
I love you so much.

08:17.070 --> 08:20.840
- Okay okay...
- He'll be back, sweetheart.

08:23.920 --> 08:26.120
I love you, Katie!

08:26.600 --> 08:27.850
Dad!

08:27.890 --> 08:29.050
Go ahead.

08:30.930 --> 08:32.650
Please drive.

08:41.900 --> 08:46.180
7 Months Later.

09:13.970 --> 09:16.090
NURSE: Jake, it's time.

09:28.190 --> 09:30.030
DOCTOR:
I'm proud of you, Jake.

09:30.470 --> 09:33.390
You need anything,
you know where to find us.

09:33.750 --> 09:35.830
Let's get you out of here.

09:45.880 --> 09:48.130
(INDISTINCT P.A. ANNOUNCEMENT)

10:10.670 --> 10:13.790
Goodbye, Jake. Good luck.

10:13.830 --> 10:14.950
Thanks.

10:29.730 --> 10:31.410
You look good.

10:33.330 --> 10:36.010
I guess electroshock agrees with me.

10:36.010 --> 10:40.620
Oh, they'd better not
have scrambled those wires.

10:40.660 --> 10:42.820
You got a Nobel Prize
in that head of yours.

10:42.860 --> 10:44.620
You mark my word.

10:44.660 --> 10:47.950
If Bellow can win it,
so can you.

10:48.190 --> 10:51.910
Thanks for the pressure.
It'll be out in five minutes.

10:51.910 --> 10:54.430
(LAUGHING)

10:55.110 --> 10:56.830
Oh, you know, I've made an effort.

10:56.870 --> 10:59.200
Well, it hasn't been an effort,
it's been a great joy for me.

10:59.240 --> 11:03.640
I've seen her,
at least once a month.

11:03.680 --> 11:05.320
(FADING)
Sometimes even more.

11:05.360 --> 11:09.530
You're gonna be absolutely...

11:18.540 --> 11:21.140
Gonna see Katie later?

11:21.180 --> 11:22.100
Yeah.

11:22.140 --> 11:24.340
Now you nervous?

11:24.340 --> 11:27.100
She's my daughter.
Why would I be nervous?

11:27.140 --> 11:29.670
You want me to come with?

11:30.470 --> 11:32.830
You really are a full-service agent.

11:33.350 --> 11:35.190
I'm a friend.

11:35.950 --> 11:37.110
We'll be fine.

11:37.150 --> 11:40.600
- Yeah?
- Yeah, thanks for picking me up there.

11:45.120 --> 11:47.200
Thanks for the lift.

11:47.610 --> 11:49.010
Take care!

12:35.930 --> 12:38.340
(HORN HONKS IN DISTANCE)

13:11.970 --> 13:14.290
(DOOR BELL RINGS)

13:14.290 --> 13:16.290
- Daddy!
- Potato Chip! Hey!

13:16.850 --> 13:18.940
- I missed you! I missed you!
- I missed you too.

13:18.980 --> 13:20.460
I told you I'd come back
and now I'm back, you see?

13:20.500 --> 13:23.020
- Well, I know. But I waited for ever.
- I know.

13:23.020 --> 13:24.980
- Are you here for good?
- For good.

13:25.020 --> 13:27.180
For ever and ever.
A big yeah.

13:27.950 --> 13:29.150
- ELIZABETH: Hey, Jake.
- KATIE: I love you!

13:29.190 --> 13:30.670
- Hey.
- Welcome back.

13:30.710 --> 13:31.790
Love you too!

13:32.550 --> 13:34.790
I have coffee and cake
on the inside.

13:34.830 --> 13:36.030
- Do you drink coffee?
- Come on in.

13:36.030 --> 13:36.470
No.

13:36.470 --> 13:38.880
Well, I'm glad to hear
you don't drink coffee.

13:38.880 --> 13:40.680
- But you eat cake?
- Yes.

13:40.720 --> 13:43.880
Okay. So let's go and
have some dessert.

13:43.920 --> 13:45.480
- Hey, William.
- Welcome back, Jake.

13:45.520 --> 13:47.930
- How's the law?
- Oh, always good.

13:50.930 --> 13:53.490
And she's been doing better
and better in school.

13:53.490 --> 13:55.770
We're very proud of her.

13:57.170 --> 13:59.260
- Dottie.
- Yes, ma'am?

13:59.300 --> 14:02.260
Could you please take Katie
to her room?

14:02.700 --> 14:03.660
Why?

14:03.700 --> 14:07.550
We're just gonna have a little chat
with daddy, okay?

14:07.750 --> 14:08.990
It's okay.

14:09.590 --> 14:14.070
Boys! Not in the house.
Go up to your rooms.

14:18.200 --> 14:19.440
What's up?

14:19.440 --> 14:21.880
WILLIAM:
Almost a year away.

14:21.920 --> 14:23.640
Seven months.

14:23.640 --> 14:27.000
Look, I, uh... I wanna
thank you both

14:27.040 --> 14:30.810
and let you know how much I appreciate
you looking after Katie. She looks terrific.

14:30.850 --> 14:32.290
I'm indescribably grateful.
Thank you.

14:32.330 --> 14:35.410
- Well, we have a safe, happy home here.
- JAKE: Yes.

14:36.250 --> 14:39.540
I guess it's been quite an adjustment,
like being back.

14:39.540 --> 14:40.860
Well, I missed her terribly.

14:40.900 --> 14:42.580
ELIZABETH: Oh yeah?

14:42.580 --> 14:44.380
- Miss Patricia?
- (GLASSES CLINKS)

14:48.430 --> 14:51.030
Being back doesn't solve that.

14:51.070 --> 14:55.350
Did you know that we were gonna have lunch
the day of her funeral?

14:55.950 --> 14:59.480
You're finally going to discuss some of the
things that have been keeping us apart.

14:59.480 --> 15:00.720
- Elizabeth...
- And...

15:00.720 --> 15:04.760
...there's not a day that
I don't think about that, Jake.

15:08.530 --> 15:13.170
She was my only sister
and I never got the chance...

15:13.170 --> 15:15.370
- Look, Elizabeth...
- I...

15:17.580 --> 15:22.140
We'd like to make a proposal, Jake,
and just hear me out.

15:22.140 --> 15:25.380
We'd like Katie stay here tonight,
and you get settled.

15:25.380 --> 15:26.940
You'll get you sea legs,
so to speak.

15:26.980 --> 15:29.190
And then, you know, in a week or
whenever you're ready,

15:29.190 --> 15:31.590
then have Katie come with you.

15:31.590 --> 15:32.150
That won't be necessary.

15:32.150 --> 15:35.870
- Well, it's no hardship for us.
- We'll be fine.

15:35.910 --> 15:38.600
- We enjoy having Katie here.
- We like having her here.

15:38.640 --> 15:40.200
You got late.

15:41.040 --> 15:42.440
Katie.

15:44.200 --> 15:47.570
We'd like to adopt Katie!

15:47.610 --> 15:48.930
What?

15:49.410 --> 15:50.850
Elizabeth, God damn it!

15:50.890 --> 15:54.450
Listen, I don't want the
kids to hear us. Let me just...

15:58.460 --> 16:00.060
What are you talking about?

16:00.060 --> 16:02.580
Look, Jake, I've never been comfortable
hiding our intentions.

16:02.620 --> 16:05.660
Look, Katie is happy here.
She loves Andrew and Michael.

16:05.700 --> 16:07.230
I mean, you should see the way the three...

16:07.230 --> 16:08.390
Katie is my daughter!

16:08.390 --> 16:11.030
Well, yeah, of course she is.
But we're very comfortable.

16:11.070 --> 16:13.550
Staying at St. Francis for a year,

16:13.550 --> 16:15.550
I imagine you ran through
most of your money.

16:15.550 --> 16:17.560
You could see her
whenever you want,

16:17.560 --> 16:20.880
and this is gonna free you up
to concentrating on your...

16:22.160 --> 16:23.440
- Katie!
- Jake.

16:23.480 --> 16:25.720
- Come on, we're going.
- BOTH: Jake! Jake!

16:29.490 --> 16:31.090
JAKE: Potato Chip.

16:31.810 --> 16:34.250
So I thought we rehearsed this.

16:34.250 --> 16:37.170
- He killed my sister, not yours.
- (WILLIAM SIGHS)

16:47.630 --> 16:48.870
Jake.

16:48.910 --> 16:51.310
- Say thank you.
- Thank you.

16:51.630 --> 16:52.710
- Say goodbye.
- Bye.

16:52.750 --> 16:54.310
Honey, I love you. Bye.

16:55.670 --> 17:03.800
- (MUSIC PLAYING)
- 25 Years Later.

17:07.079 --> 17:09.170
EVAN: Hey, Katie, wait up.

17:10.130 --> 17:12.690
- What's going on?
- Studying.

17:12.690 --> 17:15.569
Can't believe you're getting a
graduating degree in psychology,

17:15.609 --> 17:18.260
sitting around listening to people
whine about their problems all day.

17:18.260 --> 17:19.700
I like helping people.

17:19.740 --> 17:21.460
You can help me.

17:21.500 --> 17:23.260
I'm lonely as hell.

17:23.260 --> 17:25.780
What could I possibly do
to help you, Evan?

17:25.819 --> 17:28.910
I don't know. We could go out
for a date sometime.

17:29.190 --> 17:30.910
You're a confident man, huh?

17:30.950 --> 17:32.710
Am I? I think so.

17:32.750 --> 17:34.510
So tell me,
what do you really want?

17:34.550 --> 17:37.190
Do you wanna date me,
or do you wanna fuck me?

17:37.240 --> 17:39.120
'cause I'm fine either way.

17:41.920 --> 17:44.440
- What happened to your confidence?
- (EVAN CHUCKLES)

17:44.440 --> 17:48.730
- (KATIE MOANING LOUDLY)
- (EVAN MOANING)

17:50.250 --> 17:53.850
- (EVAN MOANS, CHUCKLES)
- (BOTH PANTING)

18:10.870 --> 18:13.390
Can I see you again?

18:14.230 --> 18:15.550
No, man.

18:17.440 --> 18:21.160
Why'd you do that if you don't
wanna see me again?

18:21.200 --> 18:24.160
I didn't have time
to work out today. (LAUGHS)

18:29.530 --> 18:31.730
See you around, Evan.

18:35.050 --> 18:36.730
- Hi, Mariah.
- MARIAH: Hi.

18:36.770 --> 18:38.780
- You staying out of trouble?
- I'm trying.

18:38.820 --> 18:39.980
All right.

18:43.820 --> 18:45.980
A case just got transferred to us.

18:45.980 --> 18:48.150
A 12 year old girl.

18:49.830 --> 18:51.790
Lucy Carter.

18:51.830 --> 18:54.830
Her father died when she was an infant.
Drug overdose.

18:54.830 --> 18:58.160
His mother was a prostitute
murdered by a John almost a year ago.

18:58.200 --> 18:59.560
Where's she living?

18:59.560 --> 19:02.200
Foster parents on 133rd.

19:02.600 --> 19:05.680
She hasn't spoken a word
since her mother's funeral.

19:05.720 --> 19:08.210
She hasn't spoken for a year?

19:08.890 --> 19:10.850
How was her speaking before?

19:10.850 --> 19:12.330
Just normal.

19:12.530 --> 19:14.170
Any physiological?

19:14.170 --> 19:16.250
Not a thing.

19:16.250 --> 19:18.380
Thought you might be interested.

19:19.140 --> 19:20.780
Definitely.

19:22.100 --> 19:23.260
Good.

19:26.380 --> 19:29.030
Which one's your favorite?

19:29.710 --> 19:31.470
You can just point.

19:33.030 --> 19:36.990
I like the cat.
But that's just me.

19:41.640 --> 19:44.560
Lucy, I know you're scared.

19:47.250 --> 19:51.770
But you're in a really
safe place, okay?

19:51.810 --> 19:54.610
And I wanna be here to help you.

19:54.650 --> 19:56.170
I promise you that.

20:02.620 --> 20:04.700
I...

20:04.740 --> 20:07.430
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

20:07.430 --> 20:08.910
...don't love.

20:08.950 --> 20:11.190
THERAPIST:
But you have loved.

20:12.030 --> 20:14.390
Yeah, a long time ago once.

20:14.390 --> 20:17.320
So you know that you can love?

20:19.440 --> 20:21.560
I'm... There's nothing in here.
There's nothing.

20:21.600 --> 20:25.520
It's like... It's an empty well.
It's...

20:25.520 --> 20:27.970
just dry and barren.

20:28.770 --> 20:32.570
Is that why you sleep with all these men?

20:32.730 --> 20:35.450
- No.
- So what is it you want?

20:35.490 --> 20:37.130
- I don't want anything.
- Well, you must want something,

20:37.130 --> 20:38.900
you continue to do it.

20:39.420 --> 20:40.660
(SIGHS)

20:40.660 --> 20:42.900
THERAPIST:
So how does it make you feel?

20:42.940 --> 20:44.340
- Happy?
- No.

20:44.340 --> 20:45.820
Pretty?

20:45.820 --> 20:48.070
- No!
- So what?

20:48.790 --> 20:51.310
It makes me feel...

20:53.070 --> 20:58.160
It makes me feel... something,

20:58.160 --> 21:00.360
because most of the time
I feel nothing.

21:00.360 --> 21:03.760
And these are men that
you don't even like.

21:03.760 --> 21:05.120
Right.

21:05.800 --> 21:09.930
So what would you do if you met a man
that you actually did like?

21:09.930 --> 21:11.490
I don't know.

21:13.130 --> 21:17.260
Probably make him regret the day
he laid eyes on me.

21:17.540 --> 21:19.660
(MUSIC PLAYING)

21:21.100 --> 21:22.260
BRIAN: Hey.

21:22.260 --> 21:24.900
How are you doing?
What's your name?

21:25.100 --> 21:26.140
Katie.

21:26.180 --> 21:29.230
Katie, I'm Brian.
Nice to meet you.

21:29.230 --> 21:31.070
You study here? I think I've seen
you around before.

21:31.070 --> 21:31.950
Yeah.

21:31.950 --> 21:33.870
- Awesome. What are you studying?
- Psychology.

21:33.910 --> 21:35.430
No way!
I got a buddy over there..

21:35.430 --> 21:37.960
who's just shooting pools
also studying psychology.

21:37.960 --> 21:41.040
I just took an intro course once.
I love that shit, it's like... pooh.

21:41.080 --> 21:42.080
You know.

21:42.160 --> 21:44.200
(BOTH CHUCKLES)

21:44.200 --> 21:45.920
So what are you drinking?
A Beer?

21:45.920 --> 21:47.690
Can I get you a drink?

21:47.690 --> 21:48.730
I may get you a drink.

21:48.730 --> 21:51.290
Hey, can we get two beers,
One for me, one for Katie over here?

21:51.290 --> 21:52.730
- BARTENDER: Got you.
- Thanks.

21:54.250 --> 21:55.450
So...

21:55.490 --> 21:56.770
Hmm.

21:56.770 --> 21:58.660
- Three beers already, Katie.
- (KATIE SCOFFS)

21:58.940 --> 22:01.180
Brian, you must be a math major.

22:02.060 --> 22:03.820
(CHUCKLES)
That's good, that's good.

22:05.340 --> 22:08.110
So tell me Katie,
what's your story?

22:08.150 --> 22:14.230
Well, Brian, I have very
self-destructive tendencies.

22:14.510 --> 22:16.990
- (KATIE GASPS, MOANING)
- (BRIAN MOANS, GROANS)

22:18.600 --> 22:20.880
(TELEPHONE RINGING)

22:23.680 --> 22:25.800
MAN: Hello...

22:25.800 --> 22:27.810
- TIM: William.
- Hey, Tim.

22:28.610 --> 22:30.810
Thank you, sir.

22:34.210 --> 22:36.050
- Jake.
- William.

22:36.050 --> 22:38.380
- Scotch, neat.
- Right away, sir.

22:40.020 --> 22:44.940
Elizabeth can be difficult.
Nobody knows that better than I do.

22:45.540 --> 22:47.210
(WILLIAM SIGHS)

22:47.210 --> 22:49.530
Jake, it hasn't been two years
since she lost her sister.

22:49.570 --> 22:52.690
I mean, they were very close.

22:53.410 --> 22:55.570
Tricia hated Elizabeth.

22:55.930 --> 22:58.540
Well, sisters sometimes say things...

22:58.540 --> 23:02.300
Found her controlling, selfish, judgemental.

23:02.340 --> 23:05.420
Yeah. Okay. Right. Well, listen,
we're both fairly bright guys.

23:05.460 --> 23:07.230
Let's just be frank.

23:08.390 --> 23:10.350
We proposed something that
you've got us know you had no interest.

23:10.350 --> 23:12.790
I'm not gonna bring that up again.

23:12.790 --> 23:16.030
But the reason
I asked you here today is...

23:16.070 --> 23:17.200
Thank you.

23:18.200 --> 23:23.040
Worthington called me, and they said
you're planning to pull Katie out of the school.

23:23.040 --> 23:24.680
Well, that's a mistake.

23:24.920 --> 23:29.170
I mean, if there's a better girl's school in
the country, that'd be news to me.

23:29.210 --> 23:30.850
I simply can't afford it.

23:30.890 --> 23:34.690
Please, that's our pleasure.
You're never gonna see a bill.

23:34.730 --> 23:38.900
I promise.
It's the least we can do.

23:39.300 --> 23:41.380
You've done enough already.

23:41.420 --> 23:45.180
Well, the public schools are a jungle.
Is that what you want for Katie?

23:45.220 --> 23:46.660
I'll figure something out.

23:46.700 --> 23:48.870
Well, like what?
There's public and there's private.

23:48.910 --> 23:50.910
Those are the options.

23:52.710 --> 23:54.470
You all right?

23:55.070 --> 23:56.960
I mean that...

23:57.000 --> 24:01.360
You know how difficult it is to get a kid
into a good private school in New York?

24:01.360 --> 24:05.720
Everybody's rich that applies,
and they're connected and underhanded.

24:06.770 --> 24:09.250
I'll figure something out.
Let me buy you a drink.

24:09.290 --> 24:11.530
- You'll not...
- Jake.

24:12.170 --> 24:16.090
You'll not be raising
my daughter by committing.

24:58.180 --> 25:00.260
(SIRENS WAILING IN A DISTANCE)

25:11.190 --> 25:13.390
(HORNS HONKING IN A DISTANCE)

25:28.970 --> 25:31.090
You like my bike?

25:31.810 --> 25:34.930
I used to have a pink bike
when I was a little girl.

25:36.250 --> 25:38.380
Do you know how to ride?

25:38.420 --> 25:40.660
Do you know how to ride a bike?

25:41.780 --> 25:44.540
Do any of your friends have bikes?

25:51.030 --> 25:54.950
If you want, one day I can take you out
and teach you how to ride.

25:54.990 --> 25:59.360
We could go out to the park
one of these days.

26:01.280 --> 26:02.960
It could be fun.

26:05.800 --> 26:08.250
So how's it going with Lucy?
Is she talking?

26:08.290 --> 26:09.850
It's a process.

26:09.890 --> 26:11.490
So she's not talking.

26:11.490 --> 26:14.730
Look, I'm going to transfer
the case to Dr. Weinberg,

26:14.730 --> 26:16.290
she's a very experienced
psychologist.

26:16.290 --> 26:18.260
I just need more time.

26:18.300 --> 26:21.660
And I need something to put
into her sixty-day report.

26:22.020 --> 26:26.420
Look, this isn't about trying
to impress the state agency

26:26.420 --> 26:29.590
that just so happens to fund us
at a time of severe cutbacks.

26:29.590 --> 26:31.590
It's about helping this little girl...

26:31.590 --> 26:33.630
who's suffered such severe trauma
she can't even speak anymore,

26:33.630 --> 26:38.600
and will live an unbearably bleak life
if we don't connect with her, and soon.

26:39.400 --> 26:42.720
Now we've failed her,
and we have to fix it.

26:42.720 --> 26:44.800
We've not failed her.

26:44.800 --> 26:47.810
Katie, you're a very
bright young woman.

26:47.850 --> 26:51.210
You're gonna be an exceptional
psychologist someday.

26:51.250 --> 26:54.530
But you need to know when
to admit defeat, and move on.

26:54.570 --> 26:57.100
Let me take her to the park, okay?

26:57.140 --> 27:02.180
- I think a different environment should just...
- There's no environment, as therapist.

27:02.460 --> 27:07.270
You know we can't let you take her off grounds.
But you got your week.

27:09.070 --> 27:09.870
Thanks.

27:09.910 --> 27:11.990
Katie? A week is a week!

27:12.030 --> 27:13.230
Yep.

27:14.270 --> 27:16.800
- (DOOR CLOSES)
- (INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

27:27.290 --> 27:29.610
- Jake! Hi.
- Hey.

27:29.650 --> 27:31.930
Ah, it is so good to see you again.

27:31.970 --> 27:34.330
- Pleased to meet you again.
- Yeah, of course, of course.

27:34.370 --> 27:35.810
Why don't you come on back?

27:35.850 --> 27:39.700
I just wanna tell you again
how sorry we all are about Patricia.

27:39.700 --> 27:43.900
That was a... It was just a
big loss for our whole community.

27:44.180 --> 27:45.700
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

27:45.700 --> 27:47.630
How's Katie doing?

27:47.630 --> 27:49.390
- She's fine.
- Yeah?

27:49.390 --> 27:51.950
When she left Copen, she moved in
with her aunt and uncle?

27:51.950 --> 27:52.790
- Yeah.
- Yeah?

27:52.830 --> 27:55.670
- But she's back with me now.
- Oh, good, good.

27:55.950 --> 28:00.480
And, uh... I would really like her
to come back to Copen.

28:00.520 --> 28:02.680
Well, it's the middle of the year,
you know.

28:02.720 --> 28:04.960
Do you really think pulling her out of
Worthington is the best thing right now?

28:05.000 --> 28:06.560
I already did.

28:06.560 --> 28:09.890
Oh! Uh... Gosh!

28:09.930 --> 28:12.410
Look, Jake you know we would really love
to have Katie back with us,

28:12.450 --> 28:15.570
but... we're completely full.

28:16.370 --> 28:18.540
Always room for one more.

28:18.580 --> 28:20.860
(SIGHS) Ah, it's just, um...

28:20.900 --> 28:21.900
I'm sorry.

28:21.940 --> 28:23.540
What about faculty?

28:23.580 --> 28:26.180
- What about them?
- The faculty get priority for admission.

28:26.180 --> 28:27.990
Ah, yes and free to...

28:28.030 --> 28:31.550
I will teach creative writing
for seniors.

28:31.550 --> 28:33.830
Ah, okay. Well, I don't think we're
budgeted for something like that.

28:33.830 --> 28:35.310
For a dollar a semester.

28:35.350 --> 28:37.560
Jake, I appreciate it,
I really do.

28:37.600 --> 28:39.240
Um, the craft of short story?

28:39.240 --> 28:44.200
We'll focus on student work,
study of the masters,

28:44.240 --> 28:46.680
Twain, Hemingway, Roth and...

28:46.730 --> 28:49.210
maybe a piece
I'm currently working on.

28:49.250 --> 28:51.730
Okay, you really wanna teach
creative writing to 12th graders?

28:51.770 --> 28:55.530
I really want my daughter
to go to Copen.

28:55.890 --> 28:58.180
And you'd write recommendations
for the college applications?

28:58.220 --> 29:01.940
If any student shows,
then talent them.

29:01.980 --> 29:05.900
Talent being generously defined.

29:17.280 --> 29:19.080
Katie can start next week.

29:20.480 --> 29:22.160
Can you start next semester?

29:22.200 --> 29:23.760
I can indeed.

29:26.640 --> 29:28.010
Thank you.

29:28.650 --> 29:31.170
Do you know what my
favorite part of the day is?

29:31.170 --> 29:35.090
- What?
- This part, taking you to school.

29:36.490 --> 29:38.860
(CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING)

29:49.550 --> 29:52.070
(TELEPHONE RINGING)

29:52.710 --> 29:54.070
I'm working.

30:04.920 --> 30:06.160
Hello?

30:06.200 --> 30:08.610
ELIZABETH: (ON PHONE)
Hi, Jake, it's Elizabeth calling.

30:09.810 --> 30:11.290
Hey, Elizabeth.

30:12.370 --> 30:13.490
Hi. Um...

30:14.170 --> 30:17.780
I'm calling to invite you and Katie
over for dinner.

30:18.420 --> 30:20.340
What day would work for you?

30:20.340 --> 30:23.020
(STAMMERING)
How does Thursday sound?

30:23.060 --> 30:25.660
Uh, no. Look,
Thursday I'm on a writer's panel.

30:25.700 --> 30:27.110
What about Saturday?

30:27.110 --> 30:29.910
Dottie's making her meatloaf,
it's Katie favorite.

30:29.950 --> 30:31.710
Yeah? Oh, she would love that.

30:31.710 --> 30:33.750
You know, but Saturday, you see,
we're going to the park,

30:33.750 --> 30:36.190
she's gonna get
really tired afterwards.

30:36.920 --> 30:40.640
Listen Jake, stop playing games
with me, all right?

30:41.200 --> 30:44.120
Katie lived with us for a year.

30:44.280 --> 30:48.490
The boys miss her terribly,
as do William and I.

30:48.770 --> 30:51.210
Now are you going to come
to dinner or not?

30:51.350 --> 30:52.630
I said yes.

30:52.670 --> 30:56.960
All right then, we should set a date
that works for you.

30:57.000 --> 30:58.520
Hey...

30:58.560 --> 31:01.800
Elizabeth, look, I'm writing at the moment.
Can I call you back? Thanks.

31:03.040 --> 31:05.240
(SIGHS)

31:19.620 --> 31:20.900
Come in.

31:21.180 --> 31:23.580
- Hey.
- Well, hey there.

31:25.900 --> 31:28.190
I have a gift for you.

31:29.270 --> 31:31.310
But that's not necessary.

31:36.070 --> 31:41.080
You didn't think I spent the whole time
in the hospital basket-living, did you?

31:41.640 --> 31:43.520
Bitter Tulips?

31:45.440 --> 31:48.770
Hmm. I like it.

31:49.570 --> 31:51.610
Any good?

31:51.650 --> 31:53.290
Best thing I've ever written.

31:53.330 --> 31:56.090
- Really?
- Mm-hmm. I'm sure of it.

31:56.170 --> 31:58.260
(CHUCKLING)

31:58.260 --> 32:00.220
You son of a gun!

32:00.460 --> 32:02.500
I'm gonna get this sold by lunch.

32:02.540 --> 32:06.020
Good, because I'm broke.
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

32:08.190 --> 32:11.590
KATIE: I thought it'd be nice
to take a break from the office.

32:11.630 --> 32:14.470
Sit here and watch the ducks
go about their day?

32:16.110 --> 32:18.600
(DUCKS QUACKING)

32:19.640 --> 32:23.800
In my next life,
I wanna come back as a duck.

32:25.200 --> 32:27.850
You can fly, you can swim.

32:29.650 --> 32:31.530
You can quack.

32:36.380 --> 32:38.180
Pretty nice.

32:57.320 --> 33:00.760
She sat there and held my hand.

33:00.760 --> 33:02.960
She held my hand.

33:02.960 --> 33:04.840
Where did this happen?

33:04.880 --> 33:06.650
In my office.

33:06.970 --> 33:10.570
- But... she didn't speak?
- No.

33:10.610 --> 33:12.610
So I'm transferring her
to Dr. Weinberg.

33:13.810 --> 33:16.580
- We are on the verge.
- What does "on the verge" mean?

33:16.620 --> 33:18.140
A week? A month?
A year? What?

33:18.180 --> 33:20.300
It means that we are
making progress.

33:20.340 --> 33:21.900
I'm sorry, Katie.

33:22.300 --> 33:24.820
- That's not fair!
- It's completely fair.

33:24.860 --> 33:28.670
Now you're to inform Lucy
that Tuesday's session will be your last.

33:28.710 --> 33:33.350
And at the end of the session, Dr. Weinberg
will come in and introduce herself.

33:33.390 --> 33:35.470
We're done here.

33:40.800 --> 33:43.600
Will you please put this back
on the shelf?

33:45.200 --> 33:46.330
Thank you.

33:49.210 --> 33:51.490
(KATIE INHALES, EXHALES)

33:52.290 --> 33:57.700
Um... Lucy, I've had the best
couple of months with you.

33:58.180 --> 34:01.220
Oh boy! It's been such a pleasure
to get to know you,

34:01.220 --> 34:05.980
and to read, and play
and draw pictures.

34:08.429 --> 34:12.429
It's been so fun that I told my friend Carla
who works here, she's super nice,

34:12.429 --> 34:14.070
how much fun it's been.

34:14.070 --> 34:18.520
And she want's to play with you too.
So she's excited to meet you.

34:18.520 --> 34:22.760
She's actually gonna come by
in a couple of minutes to say, Hi.

34:22.800 --> 34:28.250
And... next time you come here, you're
gonna hang out with her, instead of me.

34:31.409 --> 34:32.850
No.

34:38.300 --> 34:40.820
I wanna stay with you.

34:46.350 --> 34:48.550
(CHILDREN SHRIEKING,
SHOUTING)

34:55.030 --> 34:58.600
YOUNG KATIE:
Daddy! Daddy!

34:59.360 --> 35:00.880
Daddy!

35:03.040 --> 35:04.160
- JAKE: Hey!
- KATIE: Hi!

35:04.200 --> 35:05.560
How are you doing?

35:05.560 --> 35:07.250
- I've got some great news.
- What?

35:07.250 --> 35:09.450
Daddy sold a book today.

35:09.490 --> 35:12.010
- Is that good?
- Is that good? Are you kidding me!

35:12.050 --> 35:13.890
It's the greatest news in the world!

35:13.890 --> 35:18.020
That means you can have any toy
on the entire planet.

35:18.380 --> 35:20.940
- I want a bike, pink with a basket and bell,
- A bike! Pink! Basket!

35:20.980 --> 35:23.260
- and streamers dangling from the handlebar.
- Those streamers, Okay!

35:23.260 --> 35:26.390
Let's go and get that!
That's what you should have!

35:27.550 --> 35:30.830
Keep your balance.
Keep your balance by looking forward.

35:31.230 --> 35:32.590
That's it!

35:32.590 --> 35:34.190
You're going great!

35:34.230 --> 35:36.920
It's all you. It's all you!

35:36.960 --> 35:38.440
Now accelerate.

35:38.720 --> 35:40.080
Here you go!

35:40.080 --> 35:42.640
Here you go. Keep your eyes up!
Keep looking where you're going.

35:42.640 --> 35:43.960
That's my girl!

35:43.960 --> 35:46.160
Oh, yeah!
She's got it.

35:46.160 --> 35:47.730
She's got it!

35:47.730 --> 35:49.130
Go, Katie!

35:52.370 --> 35:53.850
Go faster!

35:55.290 --> 35:57.460
Go, Katie!

35:58.380 --> 36:00.460
That's my girl!

36:03.540 --> 36:09.710
KATIE: (SING-ALONG)
♪ Why do birds suddenly appear ♪

36:09.750 --> 36:15.430
♪ Every time you are near? ♪

36:15.470 --> 36:20.760
♪ Just like me, they long to be ♪

36:20.800 --> 36:24.840
♪ Close to you ♪

36:24.880 --> 36:31.290
KATIE & JAKE: (SING-ALONG)
♪ Why do stars fall down from the sky ♪

36:31.330 --> 36:37.060
♪ Every time you walk by? ♪

36:37.100 --> 36:42.540
♪ Just like me, they long to be ♪

36:42.580 --> 36:46.550
♪ Close to you ♪

36:48.030 --> 36:53.030
♪ On the day that you were
born the angels got together ♪

36:53.070 --> 36:58.160
♪ And decided to create
a dream come true ♪

36:58.160 --> 37:01.280
♪ So they sprinkled moon dust
in your hair ♪

37:01.280 --> 37:06.080
♪ And golden starlight
in your eyes of blue ♪

37:06.370 --> 37:08.530
(KATIE MAKES PIANO SOUNDS)

37:08.530 --> 37:14.570
♪ That is why all
the girls in town ♪

37:14.610 --> 37:16.940
♪ Follow you all around ♪

37:16.940 --> 37:18.380
What are you writing?

37:18.420 --> 37:20.780
I am writing a new book.

37:20.780 --> 37:23.020
What's it about?

37:23.460 --> 37:24.700
It's about you.

37:24.740 --> 37:25.460
Me?

37:25.500 --> 37:26.510
Mm-hmm.

37:27.830 --> 37:31.790
I've called her Potato Chip
for as long as I can remember.

37:31.830 --> 37:34.190
I've no reason why I like the name.

37:41.720 --> 37:44.280
What do you think?
You like it?

37:44.320 --> 37:46.890
Could it be about us instead?

37:46.930 --> 37:49.570
- Can it be about us?
- Yeah.

37:51.890 --> 37:55.890
You know, kiddo, you are a genius!

37:56.380 --> 37:59.740
- My daughter is a genius!
- (KATIE GIGGLES)

38:01.860 --> 38:03.420
Yeah, it can be about us.

38:03.460 --> 38:05.900
♪ So they sprinkled moon dust
in your hair ♪

38:05.900 --> 38:10.990
♪ And golden starlight
in your eyes of blue ♪

38:11.550 --> 38:14.750
(DISCO MUSIC PLAYING)

38:21.760 --> 38:22.760
Hey.

38:23.640 --> 38:24.600
You know...

38:24.640 --> 38:28.450
Normally I would never approach
someone like you, but...

38:28.490 --> 38:30.530
I heard a rumor.

38:31.170 --> 38:32.690
What rumor?

38:32.730 --> 38:38.580
Um... That my literary idol and
your father are the same person.

38:39.060 --> 38:41.300
I don't know if that's true.

38:41.340 --> 38:43.540
So they lied to me?

38:43.580 --> 38:44.460
Who?

38:44.500 --> 38:48.830
My friends, they're liars.
You're not Potato Chip?

38:48.830 --> 38:50.430
Sorry.

38:52.390 --> 38:55.750
I can't really hear you.
Can we move?

38:55.750 --> 38:57.480
Yeah.

38:58.760 --> 39:00.400
Where...

39:08.770 --> 39:11.090
What were you babbling about?

39:11.130 --> 39:11.970
Nice. Um...

39:11.970 --> 39:13.610
Jake Davis,

39:13.650 --> 39:18.780
he wrote my favorite book,
of all time, "Fathers and Daughters".

39:19.540 --> 39:22.140
Wow. It's a popular book?

39:22.140 --> 39:23.140
Yeah.

39:23.180 --> 39:27.390
I know. It's just been with me
ever since I was a little kid.

39:27.430 --> 39:29.070
It...

39:29.110 --> 39:32.550
literally changed my life. So...

39:32.790 --> 39:35.990
Hi. My name's Cameron.

39:36.360 --> 39:38.600
I'm Katie.

39:39.600 --> 39:41.160
Katie?

39:41.160 --> 39:42.200
Yes.

39:42.240 --> 39:45.720
As in, "Kate Davis"?

39:50.410 --> 39:52.570
You're the real Kate Davis?

39:54.250 --> 39:58.300
How close is the book to what
actually happened?

39:58.300 --> 40:00.540
It's a lot funnier in the book.

40:00.540 --> 40:01.500
Okay.

40:02.460 --> 40:06.870
Is this your thing?
You go out, alone, no friends?

40:06.870 --> 40:09.070
- Yeah.
- Yeah?

40:09.070 --> 40:11.950
Sometimes I really just...
I prefer being alone.

40:11.990 --> 40:14.550
It's a lot easier.

40:15.550 --> 40:17.920
So what do you do?

40:18.920 --> 40:23.080
(CHUCKLES) I'm a social worker.
I work with kids with problems.

40:23.760 --> 40:25.840
- Wow.
- Yeah.

40:25.880 --> 40:27.370
I like it.

40:30.970 --> 40:33.010
So how do you get by?

40:33.010 --> 40:36.170
I'm a freelance writer
for a few newspapers

40:36.210 --> 40:39.940
and starting my first book.

40:40.300 --> 40:42.220
What's it called?

40:42.260 --> 40:44.660
- You really wanna know?
- Yeah.

40:44.700 --> 40:48.230
Uh... "Two is the Perfect Number."

40:49.070 --> 40:51.470
- Two is the Perfect Number?
- Yeah.

40:51.510 --> 40:53.270
Is that a love story?

40:53.310 --> 40:57.320
Uh... Yeah. Kind of.

40:59.280 --> 41:01.280
This is me.

41:01.320 --> 41:03.040
- This is you.
- Yeah.

41:03.080 --> 41:05.920
Wow, this is really nice!

41:05.960 --> 41:08.290
Perfect for a Potato Chip.

41:08.350 --> 41:10.950
Well, you're never seeing
my apartment.

41:10.990 --> 41:18.720
I'm... well, not the would...
This is a... date or... anything but... uh

41:20.760 --> 41:23.320
What are you doing tomorrow?

41:23.960 --> 41:25.120
Why?

41:25.160 --> 41:29.370
Well, so we can continue
this conversation.

41:31.330 --> 41:34.410
I was, you know, running.

41:34.450 --> 41:36.020
I can run.

41:36.980 --> 41:40.020
- Would you like to join me?
- Yeah, I would.

41:40.020 --> 41:41.580
Okay.

41:42.940 --> 41:44.540
Um...

41:44.820 --> 41:46.750
Meet me up here at four.

41:46.790 --> 41:49.390
Four? Okay.

41:51.150 --> 41:53.550
Um... Sweet... Sweet dreams.

41:54.790 --> 41:57.480
Sweet dreams to you too,
Cameron.

42:01.120 --> 42:03.080
- Good night.
- KATIE: Night.

42:13.610 --> 42:17.780
JAKE: (NARRATING) The rising
moon draws the youthful eye,

42:17.820 --> 42:21.900
rising and shining,
full of grace and hope.

42:21.940 --> 42:26.670
Yes, the tulips are beautiful,
for now.

42:28.550 --> 42:34.190
Everything lives and dies,
rises and falls,

42:34.910 --> 42:37.600
and loves and leaves...

42:40.200 --> 42:43.720
(CROWD APPLAUDING)

42:52.650 --> 42:55.450
You can pre-order
"Bitter tulips" downstairs.

42:55.450 --> 43:00.580
And Mr. Davis is also graciously agreed to
sign copies of his previous books,

43:00.580 --> 43:04.700
which we've conveniently made
available to you. Thank you.

43:04.700 --> 43:06.750
(CROWD CONTINUES APPLAUDING)

43:12.230 --> 43:13.670
(CROWD CHATTERING)

43:13.670 --> 43:15.030
Kerri.

43:15.070 --> 43:15.800
JAKE: With a C?

43:15.800 --> 43:16.920
- With a K.
- Okay.

43:16.960 --> 43:19.280
K-E-R-R-I.

43:24.360 --> 43:25.600
K...

43:25.640 --> 43:28.090
K-E-R-R-I.

43:30.890 --> 43:32.050
Thank you!

43:37.820 --> 43:39.740
Make it out "To Nancy".

44:00.120 --> 44:01.520
I need a minute.

44:02.160 --> 44:03.600
Just a minute.

44:06.370 --> 44:07.490
Just a minute.

44:14.010 --> 44:15.330
Excuse me.

44:16.900 --> 44:18.060
Excuse me.

44:20.980 --> 44:22.180
Excuse me.

44:33.350 --> 44:35.630
(RATTLING, THUDDING)

44:49.050 --> 44:51.050
Mr. Davis, are you all right?

44:52.330 --> 44:55.730
(JAKE PANTING, MOANS)

44:55.940 --> 44:57.620
Mr. Davis?

44:59.260 --> 45:00.540
It's alright.

45:07.470 --> 45:09.670
("WALTZ" PLAYING)

45:18.480 --> 45:20.160
Is this how a princess dances?

45:20.200 --> 45:23.360
Yes, it is.
Exactly how a princess dances.

45:23.360 --> 45:29.050
It's called waltz. And when you're a little
bit older, I'll show you how to do it.

45:29.930 --> 45:33.650
So if I'm a princess,
Am I gonna meet a prince one day?

45:33.690 --> 45:34.930
Yeah, absolutely.

45:34.970 --> 45:36.220
When? When?

45:36.260 --> 45:39.740
I don't know when.
When the time is right.

45:39.780 --> 45:41.340
What's his name gonna be?

45:41.380 --> 45:44.100
His name is gonna be...

45:44.100 --> 45:45.460
- Prince something.
- (BOTH LAUGHS)

45:46.830 --> 45:48.910
I don't know what
his name's gonna be.

46:01.400 --> 46:03.640
(INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE)

46:37.100 --> 46:41.780
This guy is saying ten years from now
everyone will write on computers.

46:42.140 --> 46:45.140
The typewriter will go the way of
the horse and buggy.

46:45.140 --> 46:46.150
Ass.

46:47.910 --> 46:50.870
Jake, some of the reviews
of the Tulips have come in.

46:50.870 --> 46:51.870
Yeah?

46:53.990 --> 46:54.990
Bad?

46:58.120 --> 47:02.880
A book so bad it makes you wonder
if Jake Davis was really ever that good.

47:03.280 --> 47:04.480
Oh.

47:06.530 --> 47:07.890
This is awful.

47:07.890 --> 47:09.770
Well, you've had bad reviews before.

47:09.810 --> 47:12.970
Yeah, but not like this. This is just...
personal attack.

47:13.010 --> 47:14.090
It's...

47:14.090 --> 47:16.100
This is uh...

47:17.060 --> 47:18.780
No.

47:18.780 --> 47:20.300
It's a...

47:20.340 --> 47:22.300
There's got to be others, right?

47:23.060 --> 47:25.470
- He just didn't get it.
- No.

47:25.750 --> 47:29.950
So incomprehensible. All that matters
might as well be written in aramaic.

47:29.990 --> 47:31.710
Or better yet not at all.

47:32.990 --> 47:35.440
(CLEARS THROAT, LAUGHS)

47:37.400 --> 47:39.080
I've had better times

47:40.240 --> 47:41.280
Who wrote it?

47:41.320 --> 47:42.200
Colson.

47:43.200 --> 47:44.880
- He's just a little prick, right?
- Yeah.

47:44.880 --> 47:46.530
I wouldn't do the blurb for his novella.

47:46.570 --> 47:48.370
See? He's just getting some revenge.

47:48.410 --> 47:50.610
Knopf's gonna cut initial run in half.

47:50.650 --> 47:56.940
But I mean if it starts to sell what, marketing,
I think they're probably gonna cut that too.

47:56.980 --> 47:59.340
Well, if they don't support us,
it's just dead in the water.

47:59.340 --> 48:02.380
What can I...
If they are not paying for ads,

48:02.380 --> 48:05.470
if they're not putting a platform,
I can't do anything.

48:05.510 --> 48:06.910
I fought like a bastard.

48:06.910 --> 48:08.710
They do not care
what you have done.

48:08.750 --> 48:10.550
Just a bunch of bean counters.

48:11.110 --> 48:13.070
They're just reviews.

48:13.070 --> 48:15.150
It's just you know...

48:15.150 --> 48:17.560
- I don't care about reviews
- Right.

48:17.600 --> 48:19.280
All right. I'll see you later.

48:20.040 --> 48:23.280
(SIGHS)

48:26.050 --> 48:28.290
- (SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE)
- (DRILLING IN A DISTANCE)

48:40.860 --> 48:43.460
(SINGSONGY)
An arm, two arms...

48:43.580 --> 48:45.430
- You know...
- Mm-hmm?

48:45.470 --> 48:49.150
If you don't wanna go to
aunt Elizabeth's birthday,

48:49.190 --> 48:51.270
you don't have to, you know.

48:51.670 --> 48:54.470
I know, but I wanna go.

48:54.510 --> 48:55.760
- Really?
- Yep.

48:55.800 --> 49:00.480
Because we could go and do something else,
like anything you want.

49:00.520 --> 49:02.720
But daddy, I wanna go.

49:03.120 --> 49:04.640
- Really?
- Yep.

49:04.840 --> 49:07.890
- Is bribery gonna work? No?
- No.

49:11.890 --> 49:13.610
You look beautiful.

49:13.610 --> 49:14.730
Thank you.

49:15.170 --> 49:17.540
- (PIANO PLAYING)
- (CHATTERING)

49:19.060 --> 49:20.300
ELIZABETH: Katie!

49:21.340 --> 49:23.220
Hi!

49:23.220 --> 49:25.140
(LAUGHING)

49:25.140 --> 49:26.670
Finally!

49:26.710 --> 49:28.910
I missed you so much!

49:28.910 --> 49:30.870
Look who's here, kids!

50:00.140 --> 50:01.620
WILLIAM: Jake.

50:01.660 --> 50:02.780
William.

50:03.380 --> 50:05.060
Ah, thanks for coming.

50:05.470 --> 50:07.590
I'm sorry. I hear about your book.

50:07.630 --> 50:10.990
It must've been rough the way
the criticism pegged down to you.

50:11.030 --> 50:13.350
Yeah, well, you know...

50:13.350 --> 50:17.800
I don't know why God invented cockroaches
or literary critics. I'm sure he had his reasons.

50:17.840 --> 50:19.920
Well, you know, I mean,
they just hated it.

50:19.960 --> 50:22.880
I mean, they actively hated it.
How do you get passed on like that?

50:22.920 --> 50:26.250
Well, you know, pick a cellphone,
the self-affluent.

50:26.290 --> 50:27.770
That kind of thing.

50:29.490 --> 50:33.970
You know, have you even noticed...

50:34.010 --> 50:35.380
that you're shaking.

50:35.420 --> 50:39.020
The last time we met, it looked to me like
you were about to have a seizure.

50:39.020 --> 50:39.780
And I... I admit,

50:39.820 --> 50:45.180
I mean I was disturbed to see you still
wrestling with an impulses you can't control

50:45.180 --> 50:48.030
even after all that time
in the hospital.

50:48.030 --> 50:50.630
The book's prove, Jake.

50:50.630 --> 50:53.510
You're not ready for the real world.
You're not cut out to be a father.

50:53.550 --> 50:57.480
You just give Katie to somebody
actually can take care of her.

50:57.480 --> 51:00.240
Tell your kid that you love her,
and then you can't do what's best for her.

51:00.280 --> 51:01.800
That's hypocrisy at the worst.

51:03.200 --> 51:06.730
- (CHATTERING STOPS)
- (WILLIAM CHUCKLES)

51:07.210 --> 51:09.330
Carl, just not so much left-hand.

51:11.530 --> 51:13.930
That's funny, man.
That's funny.

51:15.090 --> 51:17.380
You're in deep shit now.

51:23.300 --> 51:24.700
Nice move.

51:25.350 --> 51:27.470
You'd better mind.
He's mannerless.

51:47.330 --> 51:50.690
(WINCES, GROANS)

52:03.460 --> 52:06.750
KATIE: Daddy, Sit here
and read me a book!

52:06.990 --> 52:10.950
Yeah, baby.
I'll be right there.

52:17.320 --> 52:19.520
(TYPEWRITER KEYS CLACKING)

52:37.180 --> 52:40.020
Oh, shit! Shit! Shit!

52:50.110 --> 52:51.310
Katie, your dad's here.

52:51.350 --> 52:52.510
Hey!

52:53.110 --> 52:56.480
Sorry. The train got stuck
at Park Street Station.

52:56.520 --> 52:59.160
Somebody pulled
the emergency ring. Hey.

52:59.200 --> 53:01.560
You said you would set the alarm
when you're working!

53:01.600 --> 53:03.960
I hate being the last one picked up!

53:04.640 --> 53:06.290
Potato Chip.

53:06.290 --> 53:08.050
Hey.

53:17.260 --> 53:21.020
There seems to be a very
grumpy child here.

53:21.020 --> 53:26.550
Trying to take away the grumpiness
one layer at a time.

53:29.110 --> 53:30.950
Okay.

53:30.950 --> 53:33.390
Yeah, that's a little bit
of grumpiness gone.

53:35.190 --> 53:37.840
I still see some grumpiness.

53:42.040 --> 53:44.200
Gone! It's all gone.

53:44.200 --> 53:46.250
Here I'm a pretty good doctor.

53:47.090 --> 53:49.410
KATIE: Okay.
I'll stay with you, okay?

53:50.290 --> 53:53.890
All right, I'm gonna give you a big push
and let you go, okay?

53:54.530 --> 53:55.540
Go!

53:55.580 --> 53:56.860
Go! Go!

53:56.900 --> 53:57.740
Go, Lucy!

53:57.780 --> 54:00.740
Yes! Go, keep going, Lucy. Go!

54:08.630 --> 54:11.750
That's my girl!

54:18.840 --> 54:22.920
CAMERON: You wanna know what
made me decide to become a writer?

54:22.920 --> 54:24.440
Really stick to it?

54:24.880 --> 54:26.970
Well, when I was in Kenya,

54:27.010 --> 54:31.970
one morning I woke up
and jumped out of the car, to pee,

54:31.970 --> 54:35.130
and... I was face to face with a lion.

54:35.620 --> 54:36.740
Really?

54:36.780 --> 54:38.220
Yeah, I know, for real.

54:38.260 --> 54:41.300
I mean, a male lion
about 15 feet in front of me

54:41.300 --> 54:44.140
just staring straight at me.

54:44.180 --> 54:47.990
I mean, he was clearly telling me
that I was his.

54:48.030 --> 54:49.470
What'd you do?

54:49.510 --> 54:51.270
I didn't do anything.
I was frozen.

54:51.270 --> 54:54.150
I mean, I physically could not move.

54:54.590 --> 54:57.920
You know, he stared at me for
a few more moments and he just...

54:57.920 --> 55:00.880
walked right past me.

55:02.040 --> 55:05.410
I will never forget that moment,
you know.

55:05.410 --> 55:10.010
I realized that no more plan B,

55:10.050 --> 55:13.490
no documentary, no veterinarian,

55:13.490 --> 55:15.780
no Harvard.

55:15.820 --> 55:19.220
I just wanted to do what
I always dreamed of, you know?

55:19.220 --> 55:22.620
I wanted to write, you know?

55:22.620 --> 55:29.030
I wanted to write as if every page I was writing on
was the last page before I die.

55:29.030 --> 55:30.470
You know? I wanna...

55:30.470 --> 55:32.630
I wanna leave something behind.

55:32.670 --> 55:34.470
You know? I wanna...

55:34.510 --> 55:38.440
I wanna leave my mark,
because you know what,

55:38.440 --> 55:47.770
sooner or later, in one form or another,
a lion is just gonna come and get us all.

55:48.370 --> 55:51.130
I'm so glad that he let you live.

55:52.450 --> 55:54.730
Yeah, so am I.

55:57.620 --> 55:59.060
So am I.

57:19.840 --> 57:21.440
Coming to bed?

57:21.840 --> 57:24.080
- Yeah, in a bit.
- (KEYBOARD KEYS CLACKING)

57:29.130 --> 57:31.250
I have something for you.

57:31.250 --> 57:32.410
Hmm?

57:34.130 --> 57:35.260
What?

57:38.740 --> 57:40.700
What is this?

57:45.990 --> 57:47.710
It's the original.

57:53.390 --> 57:56.080
To Katie, My Potato Chip,

57:56.640 --> 58:00.600
who I love more
than the last number.

58:04.040 --> 58:06.570
Katie I can't accept this.

58:06.570 --> 58:08.170
I want you to have it.

58:12.010 --> 58:13.770
It's a good luck charm.

58:15.140 --> 58:16.460
It's for you.

58:32.590 --> 58:35.120
- You can't catch me.
- Yep.

58:35.160 --> 58:36.200
No, you can't.

58:36.240 --> 58:37.320
I'm on this side.

58:37.360 --> 58:40.200
- Well, I bet I can go faster than you.
- No, no. I'm on this side.

58:41.280 --> 58:42.240
I go faster than you.

58:42.280 --> 58:43.200
Come on then.

58:43.880 --> 58:44.720
Race.

58:44.720 --> 58:45.490
Okay!

58:48.010 --> 58:50.370
- Yeah! Up the bridge.
- Up the bridge.

58:51.210 --> 58:52.450
Come on!

58:54.650 --> 58:56.220
Daddy, wait!

58:56.420 --> 58:57.540
- Come on baby.
- (KATIE SHRIEKS)

59:00.660 --> 59:02.260
Up the bridge.

59:05.230 --> 59:06.950
I got it!

59:07.230 --> 59:09.030
Right. Don't forget to round that.

59:09.030 --> 59:10.350
We're gonna go round the turn.

59:10.350 --> 59:11.670
- Okay.
- Here we go.

59:12.190 --> 59:13.670
Around the turn.

59:14.470 --> 59:15.720
And another time.

59:19.640 --> 59:24.520
I can't believe I have a daughter
who puts ketchup on a hot dog.

59:25.410 --> 59:26.850
You don't like ketchup?

59:27.530 --> 59:30.290
On hamburgers, on French fries.

59:30.330 --> 59:32.010
On a hot dog? Ridiculous.

59:32.530 --> 59:34.290
Well, I'm my own person.

59:35.340 --> 59:37.940
Yeah, you are.

59:38.380 --> 59:41.140
MEN: (SINGING)
Happy birthday!

59:42.220 --> 59:46.670
Happy birthday to you.
Happy birthday to you.

59:47.230 --> 59:49.670
Happy birthday. Dear, Katie.

59:52.230 --> 59:54.550
- Happy birthday to you!
- (KATIE LAUGHS)

59:54.550 --> 59:56.640
(CUSTUMERS APPLAUDING)

59:57.020 --> 59:58.300
Thanks, guys.

59:58.620 --> 01:00:00.420
- Make a wish?
- Yeah.

01:00:04.410 --> 01:00:06.650
- Happy birthday, Katie!
- (CONTINUES APPLAUDING)

01:00:08.210 --> 01:00:10.410
- Happy birthday, Potato Chip.
- I love you.

01:00:11.930 --> 01:00:15.020
Wow, look at those teeth.

01:00:15.940 --> 01:00:21.140
I bet you all the other dinosaurs didn't
wanna bump into this guy at dinner time.

01:00:35.360 --> 01:00:36.720
Miss your mom?

01:00:38.920 --> 01:00:40.040
Me too.

01:00:49.770 --> 01:00:51.090
Hey...

01:00:55.020 --> 01:00:59.300
You know you were the great joy
in light of your mom's life,

01:00:59.340 --> 01:01:02.580
just like you're the great
joy in light of mine.

01:01:04.230 --> 01:01:05.350
(CRYING)
I really miss her.

01:01:05.350 --> 01:01:07.030
Ooh, of course you do.

01:01:07.230 --> 01:01:08.510
Of course you do.

01:01:09.790 --> 01:01:11.350
But you know what?

01:01:11.350 --> 01:01:14.600
Your mom is wherever you are.

01:01:16.160 --> 01:01:17.880
She's in this room right now.

01:01:17.880 --> 01:01:19.120
She's watching over us.

01:01:19.160 --> 01:01:20.600
She's looking down.

01:01:20.600 --> 01:01:23.970
She's got a big smile on her face
and she's so proud.

01:01:24.010 --> 01:01:26.290
She's so proud of you baby.

01:01:26.290 --> 01:01:31.490
'cause she can see the intelligent,
caring, beautiful little girl you are.

01:01:32.970 --> 01:01:33.900
Yeah.

01:01:35.820 --> 01:01:36.980
Baby.

01:01:38.620 --> 01:01:40.580
Are you going to die?

01:01:42.820 --> 01:01:44.230
Not for a very very long time,

01:01:44.230 --> 01:01:46.830
when I'm an old old old man.

01:01:47.230 --> 01:01:48.630
How old?

01:01:49.150 --> 01:01:51.910
Well, probably about...

01:01:51.950 --> 01:01:52.910
a thousand.

01:01:52.950 --> 01:01:53.840
Yeah.

01:01:53.840 --> 01:01:56.800
Yeah. Maybe a million,
if I stop eating hot dogs.

01:01:57.080 --> 01:01:59.040
Daddy?

01:01:59.880 --> 01:02:04.490
I will be such an old man, all right?

01:02:04.530 --> 01:02:07.010
You'll have your own house
and your own husband.

01:02:07.050 --> 01:02:08.290
You'll have a whole
bunch of kids.

01:02:08.330 --> 01:02:10.050
You'll have a dog and a cat

01:02:10.090 --> 01:02:13.170
and everybody will be running around
putting ketch-up on everything.

01:02:18.700 --> 01:02:20.060
Promise.

01:02:21.860 --> 01:02:23.140
I promise.

01:02:23.500 --> 01:02:25.710
Pinky swear?

01:02:28.750 --> 01:02:30.310
Pinky swear.

01:02:37.800 --> 01:02:39.080
MAN: Jake Davis?

01:02:39.920 --> 01:02:40.960
Yeah.

01:02:42.080 --> 01:02:43.890
You've been served.

01:02:49.810 --> 01:02:52.690
I have to admit I was shocked
when Bob shared your case with me.

01:02:52.730 --> 01:02:56.580
It's unprecedented for an aunt and uncle
to sue for the custody of their niece

01:02:56.620 --> 01:02:59.780
when the biological father
is not only alive and well.

01:03:00.500 --> 01:03:01.940
The famous author of The Boot.

01:03:01.980 --> 01:03:05.830
Jake, John Wilton is the best
custody lawyer in the country.

01:03:05.870 --> 01:03:08.950
I can't tell you how happy
I am he sent us your case.

01:03:08.990 --> 01:03:14.560
Sometimes these cases more about hurt feelings
than a geniune desire to obtain custody.

01:03:15.640 --> 01:03:20.040
First step is for you to sit down with William,
try and talk him out of pursuing this.

01:03:20.920 --> 01:03:22.680
And if he refuses to drop it?

01:03:22.720 --> 01:03:24.730
We'll file a motion to dismiss,

01:03:24.770 --> 01:03:27.050
argue the case is completely without merit.

01:03:27.810 --> 01:03:29.210
And if that fails?

01:03:29.850 --> 01:03:31.410
We'll kick their ass in court.

01:03:46.990 --> 01:03:47.990
Jake.

01:03:48.030 --> 01:03:49.070
Scotch, neat.

01:03:49.110 --> 01:03:50.230
WAITER: Right away, sir.

01:03:59.480 --> 01:04:00.680
I'll start.

01:04:02.040 --> 01:04:06.410
Look, I want you to know it's
not a vendetta against you.

01:04:07.610 --> 01:04:09.610
We don't blame you for
what happened to Patricia

01:04:09.650 --> 01:04:13.250
and we're not retaliating
because you kept Katie

01:04:13.250 --> 01:04:17.220
away from us after we took care
of her for a year in your absence.

01:04:18.300 --> 01:04:21.620
Our only concern is Katie's welfare.

01:04:23.060 --> 01:04:26.750
And if you asked her, she tells you in a
heartbeat she wants to stay with me?

01:04:26.790 --> 01:04:28.110
Well, she's eight.

01:04:29.950 --> 01:04:31.790
It's inadmissible in court.

01:04:32.230 --> 01:04:33.710
It still matters.

01:04:35.040 --> 01:04:37.000
You're a reasonable man, William.

01:04:37.960 --> 01:04:39.400
And you're a father.

01:04:42.040 --> 01:04:45.570
I know that in your heart you
know what you're doing is wrong.

01:04:46.330 --> 01:04:52.610
Now I admit, I was angry
when I came to pick up Katie

01:04:52.650 --> 01:04:55.780
and you talked of adopting her
out from under me.

01:04:56.540 --> 01:05:01.380
And perhaps, at the party
I overreacted.

01:05:02.860 --> 01:05:05.590
Perhaps, you overreacted?

01:05:06.670 --> 01:05:09.630
I'm truly sorry for what
happened at Elizabeth's party.

01:05:10.390 --> 01:05:11.870
You provoked me,

01:05:11.910 --> 01:05:14.960
but that still doesn't
justify my action.

01:05:15.000 --> 01:05:22.600
And I would welcome
you and Elizabeth

01:05:22.640 --> 01:05:25.010
being more involved
in Katie's life.

01:05:25.010 --> 01:05:26.770
Jake, I...

01:05:27.930 --> 01:05:31.010
Hey, I didn't file the lawsuit
as a bargaining chip.

01:05:31.650 --> 01:05:33.730
You know my lawyer John Wilton.

01:05:34.340 --> 01:05:35.780
He's a great attorney.

01:05:36.500 --> 01:05:37.780
He's not cheap.

01:05:38.580 --> 01:05:40.620
He tells me you
don't have a shot.

01:05:41.380 --> 01:05:46.630
He tells me they'll never separate a
daughter from her sole biological parent.

01:05:48.190 --> 01:05:50.030
You know you're gonna
lose, why do this?

01:05:50.030 --> 01:05:53.030
You spent a year in a mental institution
which did nothing

01:05:53.030 --> 01:05:55.160
to relieve you of your
psychotic breaks.

01:05:56.040 --> 01:06:01.760
3 dozen people witnessed you attack me
in my home at a birthday party

01:06:01.800 --> 01:06:04.090
'cause I didn't like your last book.

01:06:04.970 --> 01:06:08.010
You gave testimony to the Connecticut
state police that you were having

01:06:08.010 --> 01:06:12.050
a heated argument and speeding
at the time of your wife's death

01:06:12.050 --> 01:06:13.980
and while they didn't charge you
with reckless endangerment

01:06:13.980 --> 01:06:18.140
that is how it's gonna appear
to the custody judge.

01:06:19.700 --> 01:06:21.460
Your last book tanked,

01:06:21.460 --> 01:06:24.070
critically and commercially,
putting into doubt

01:06:24.070 --> 01:06:27.350
whether or not you can even
provide for Katie.

01:06:27.870 --> 01:06:30.590
And I've got a feeling
you're running out of money.

01:06:31.790 --> 01:06:35.120
But I'll know soon enough when I
subpoena you for national records.

01:06:39.080 --> 01:06:41.240
I got more money than God.

01:06:41.280 --> 01:06:43.930
If we lose, we'll appeal.

01:06:43.970 --> 01:06:47.210
If we lose the appeal,
we'll appeal that.

01:06:50.650 --> 01:06:54.100
How are you positioned to handle
a prolonged legal battle?

01:06:56.820 --> 01:06:59.540
You are a very good
lawyer, William.

01:07:01.340 --> 01:07:03.790
I'm trying to be a
very good uncle.

01:07:05.510 --> 01:07:08.990
No, what you're trying to do?

01:07:09.030 --> 01:07:12.070
Is you're trying to separate
a little girl

01:07:12.110 --> 01:07:15.520
who's already suffering deeply
from the loss of her mother,

01:07:15.560 --> 01:07:17.960
away from the father she loves

01:07:17.960 --> 01:07:19.680
and who loves her.

