01:28:29.250 --> 01:28:31.210
- Listen, I don't know how to do this.
- What? What?

01:28:31.210 --> 01:28:32.170
What?

01:28:32.210 --> 01:28:33.660
Do what? Do what?!

01:28:34.060 --> 01:28:35.220
I'm sorry I made a mistake

01:28:35.220 --> 01:28:36.140
You made a mistake?

01:28:36.180 --> 01:28:38.420
You let some guy
come between your legs!

01:28:38.420 --> 01:28:41.540
This's not a mistake, Kate!

01:28:42.020 --> 01:28:43.870
All right? We're done!

01:28:44.230 --> 01:28:46.750
We're done, stop, God!

01:28:47.510 --> 01:28:52.550
- (KATIE SOBBING)
- (STARTS ENGINE)

01:28:52.550 --> 01:28:53.600
Please!

01:28:53.640 --> 01:28:54.560
Stop!

01:28:55.520 --> 01:28:58.120
(TYRES SCREECHING)

01:28:58.520 --> 01:29:01.000
(SOBBING, SCREAMS)
Oh, Shit!

01:29:03.240 --> 01:29:04.650
Oh, no.

01:30:21.200 --> 01:30:22.200
Hey.

01:30:22.560 --> 01:30:26.210
You should come back
with me and Janine.

01:30:27.610 --> 01:30:30.170
(MAN LAUGHING)

01:30:32.810 --> 01:30:34.020
I'd like that.

01:30:34.620 --> 01:30:37.100
(JANINE LAUGHING)
Cool. Let's go.

01:30:40.060 --> 01:30:40.900
MAN: Are you coming?

01:30:40.900 --> 01:30:41.980
I'm coming.

01:31:09.650 --> 01:31:18.000
("CLOSE TO YOU" PLAYING)

01:31:27.000 --> 01:31:28.000
Are you coming?

01:31:28.170 --> 01:31:28.850
(SHOUTS) Go!

01:31:28.890 --> 01:31:29.810
Oh, okay.

01:31:48.190 --> 01:31:50.670
(SOBBING)

01:31:59.520 --> 01:32:01.680
I miss you.

01:32:17.380 --> 01:32:19.180
Can you call me a cab?

01:32:32.190 --> 01:32:33.160
KATIE: Hi.

01:32:35.360 --> 01:32:36.240
Hey.

01:32:37.960 --> 01:32:38.960
What're you doing up?

01:32:39.000 --> 01:32:40.160
It's morning.

01:32:40.880 --> 01:32:42.040
It's morning?

01:32:50.690 --> 01:32:52.820
Could you read me just one book?

01:33:00.140 --> 01:33:02.460
Why don't I read you all of them?

01:33:07.070 --> 01:33:08.350
Hey.

01:33:08.350 --> 01:33:09.950
You wanted to see me?

01:33:13.960 --> 01:33:15.480
Well...

01:33:16.480 --> 01:33:19.280
We have some...

01:33:20.280 --> 01:33:22.080
We have some great news.

01:33:22.720 --> 01:33:24.570
Lucy's leaving foster care.

01:33:24.610 --> 01:33:26.210
She's been adopted.

01:33:26.730 --> 01:33:27.410
Oh my god!

01:33:27.450 --> 01:33:30.450
By a loving stable family in Queens.

01:33:30.450 --> 01:33:32.940
They have two other children,
it's a perfect fit.

01:33:33.460 --> 01:33:34.420
Queens?

01:33:35.580 --> 01:33:38.180
Takes over an hour's subway to get here.

01:33:38.740 --> 01:33:40.020
Uh...

01:33:40.620 --> 01:33:41.740
Wow.

01:33:42.220 --> 01:33:43.790
Look,

01:33:48.110 --> 01:33:50.190
You can't see her anymore.

01:33:53.160 --> 01:33:53.800
What?

01:33:53.800 --> 01:33:59.000
She'll continue therapy with a social worker
who helps integrate her into her new community.

01:33:59.040 --> 01:34:01.600
She needs a clean break from us.

01:34:02.600 --> 01:34:03.850
You've done great work with her.

01:34:03.850 --> 01:34:06.010
Honey, we're all very proud.

01:34:06.770 --> 01:34:09.850
But, she can't start her new life
holding on to you.

01:34:10.690 --> 01:34:12.490
This is standard procedure.

01:34:13.140 --> 01:34:13.900
There's got to be a way...

01:34:13.940 --> 01:34:17.860
This isn't like
taking Lucy to the park.

01:34:19.380 --> 01:34:21.940
There's no way for me
to fudge this. I'm sorry.

01:34:23.910 --> 01:34:27.190
Hey, this is great news.

01:34:27.190 --> 01:34:29.510
This is what we hope and pray for.

01:34:46.370 --> 01:34:48.850
(SIGHS) We have enough a lot
to talk about huh?

01:34:51.690 --> 01:34:53.060
New family.

01:34:54.420 --> 01:34:55.860
New school.

01:35:04.430 --> 01:35:06.550
Everything's gonna be okay.

01:35:09.070 --> 01:35:10.390
I promise.

01:35:11.390 --> 01:35:13.880
- (SLAPS)
- (GASPS)

01:35:27.410 --> 01:35:29.850
I don't remember
my mother much, but...

01:35:29.850 --> 01:35:34.980
I love, love, love, my father.

01:35:35.860 --> 01:35:37.100
He was a writer.

01:35:37.860 --> 01:35:39.820
He was actually quite famous.

01:35:40.820 --> 01:35:44.910
He wasn't so, uh... mentally,

01:35:44.910 --> 01:35:47.270
but he stayed up all night every night,

01:35:47.310 --> 01:35:49.270
finishing one last book.

01:35:50.150 --> 01:35:51.950
That book was about me.

01:35:53.600 --> 01:35:56.200
But really it was about life,

01:35:56.240 --> 01:36:00.080
and how he never gave up on me.

01:36:02.890 --> 01:36:06.530
It was his way of...

01:36:06.530 --> 01:36:09.370
telling me how much he loved me.

01:36:10.970 --> 01:36:12.730
And goodbye.

01:36:14.300 --> 01:36:17.980
That's what this book
is really about. It's...

01:36:18.660 --> 01:36:22.060
never ever give up.

01:36:23.030 --> 01:36:30.390
Life's gonna be really
challenging and unfair,

01:36:30.390 --> 01:36:34.040
and sometimes painful.

01:36:34.640 --> 01:36:38.840
I mean, you've been through
a lot already,

01:36:39.320 --> 01:36:44.890
but we can never give up
or stop moving forward or looking ahead,

01:36:44.930 --> 01:36:49.530
no matter how hard the experiences
that we've been through are.

01:36:53.780 --> 01:36:57.100
All I can do is tell you that.

01:36:59.020 --> 01:37:00.500
I love you.

01:37:02.660 --> 01:37:04.430
And goodbye.

01:37:06.350 --> 01:37:07.670
I love you too.

01:37:15.400 --> 01:37:17.400
(VOICE BREAKING)
You be good, okay?

01:37:18.560 --> 01:37:21.320
You have great things
in front of you.

01:37:23.090 --> 01:37:24.330
I will.

01:37:25.410 --> 01:37:26.850
I promise.

01:37:44.750 --> 01:37:46.390
Congratulations, Jake.

01:37:46.390 --> 01:37:47.350
What for?

01:37:47.990 --> 01:37:49.470
You're gonna be an uncle again.

01:37:49.510 --> 01:37:54.200
It seems your brother-in-law William
has been having an affair with his secretary.

01:37:54.240 --> 01:37:55.360
Who's only 24.

01:37:55.360 --> 01:37:57.000
And she's pregnant.

01:37:57.000 --> 01:37:58.960
And she's keeping it.

01:37:59.000 --> 01:38:01.240
Elizabeth's filing for divorce.

01:38:01.720 --> 01:38:02.760
They dropped the suit.

01:38:02.810 --> 01:38:04.690
- BOTH: Oops!
- (BOTH LAUGHING)

01:38:11.530 --> 01:38:13.540
Fathers and Daughters.

01:38:17.300 --> 01:38:23.030
How do you write a novel in three months?
Usually takes you years.

01:38:25.070 --> 01:38:26.510
Is it any good?

01:38:28.950 --> 01:38:30.110
No idea.

01:38:32.510 --> 01:38:35.760
That's what you said to me when you
brought me Living the Dance.

01:38:37.120 --> 01:38:38.600
I brought you what?

01:38:41.400 --> 01:38:45.730
When you brought me Living the Dance,
the book you won the Pulitzer prize for.

01:38:57.780 --> 01:38:59.100
Oh, God!

01:39:46.670 --> 01:39:49.150
(GROANS)

01:39:58.680 --> 01:40:01.040
(CHOKING)

01:40:56.740 --> 01:40:59.300
(CROWS CAWING)

01:41:08.230 --> 01:41:11.430
Do you wanna say something
to your father?

01:41:26.490 --> 01:41:28.490
You're my Potato Chip.

01:41:30.290 --> 01:41:33.140
You and no one else.

01:42:33.920 --> 01:42:35.560
Hi, sweetheart.

01:43:12.880 --> 01:43:15.360
(RINGING)

01:44:45.970 --> 01:44:48.290
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

01:45:21.000 --> 01:45:23.290
(SIGHS HEAVILY)

01:45:32.210 --> 01:45:33.180
- Hey.
- Hi.

01:45:35.620 --> 01:45:36.900
I miss you.

01:45:39.300 --> 01:45:40.580
And I love you.

01:45:43.430 --> 01:45:45.670
God I love you so much.

01:45:47.230 --> 01:45:49.630
I should've said it
a million times.

01:45:49.630 --> 01:45:51.510
Yeah, I really should've.

01:45:54.040 --> 01:45:56.720
I was so afraid of you leaving me.

01:45:58.640 --> 01:46:02.480
And I know we both know
that I'm not easy.

01:46:02.480 --> 01:46:04.130
I know I'm not.

01:46:05.050 --> 01:46:06.410
And...

01:46:08.690 --> 01:46:11.650
You're the best thing that
ever happened to me.

01:46:12.610 --> 01:46:14.620
And you know what, I can't...

01:46:15.060 --> 01:46:17.220
I don't wanna live without you.

01:46:17.260 --> 01:46:21.220
WOMAN:
Cameron, I can go.

01:46:22.140 --> 01:46:25.230
It's my friend.

01:46:29.910 --> 01:46:34.520
Thank you.
Thank you for everything.

01:46:34.960 --> 01:46:36.000
Really.

01:46:38.480 --> 01:46:39.520
Katie.

01:46:41.040 --> 01:46:42.040
Katie.

01:47:02.950 --> 01:47:10.190
It is a great honor to accept this Pulitzer
on behalf of my client, the late Jake Davis.

01:47:10.190 --> 01:47:14.560
That Fathers and Daughters
has won every major literary award

01:47:14.560 --> 01:47:17.560
and been perched to top
the best sellers' list for a year

01:47:17.560 --> 01:47:20.480
is every agent's dream.

01:47:22.120 --> 01:47:26.090
That I never got to buy Jake a drink
and slap him on the back

01:47:26.130 --> 01:47:28.730
is my own personal nightmare.

01:47:30.250 --> 01:47:34.180
Katie, I think you're the only person in the world
who will miss him more than I will.

01:47:35.740 --> 01:47:38.020
- Thank you. Thank you.
- (CROWD APPLAUDING)

01:47:44.150 --> 01:47:47.630
(MUFFLED LAUGHING, CHATTERING)

01:48:03.890 --> 01:48:05.890
ELIZABETH:
I've had a hard life.

01:48:07.770 --> 01:48:12.330
I suppose I was hard right back.

01:48:15.180 --> 01:48:18.420
I'm a grown woman
who's never known love.

01:48:19.740 --> 01:48:21.420
Isn't that something?

01:48:27.950 --> 01:48:30.230
My parents were just the same,

01:48:30.270 --> 01:48:33.400
my mother was a terribly mean woman.

01:48:34.480 --> 01:48:39.680
And my father, someone we saw
at the occasional Sunday dinner.

01:48:42.680 --> 01:48:44.650
You know Katie.

01:48:44.690 --> 01:48:46.970
Men...

01:48:47.010 --> 01:48:49.810
...they can survive without love.

01:48:51.890 --> 01:48:53.940
but not us women.

01:49:37.780 --> 01:49:39.100
Come here.

